size.title: Icon Size
size.description: Set the default icon size. Set to false to disable the sizing of icon in style.

aliases.title: Icon aliases
aliases.description: Define Icon aliases to update them easily without code changes.

iconifyApiOptions.title: Iconify API Options
iconifyApiOptions.description: Define preferences for Iconify API fetch.

url.title: Iconify API URL
url.description: Define a custom Iconify API URL. Useful if you want to use a self-hosted Iconify API. Learn more: https://iconify.design/docs/api.

publicApiFallback.title: Public Iconify API fallback
publicApiFallback.description: Define if the public Iconify API should be used as fallback.

props.name: type
props.description:
Type of the container,
bounded to "note", "warning", and "error".

props.name: title
props.description:
Title of the container when specified,
default title based on type otherwise.

props.name: icon
props.description:
Custom icon of the container when specified, 
default icon based on type otherwise.

props.name: expanded
props.description: Flag to indicate if expanded

props.name: activeClass
props.description: Class to apply when the link is active

props.name: exactActiveClass
props.description: Class to apply when the link is exact active

props.name: prefetchedClass
props.description: A class to apply to links that have been prefetched.

props.name: to
props.description: Route Location the link should navigate to when clicked on.

props.name: custom
props.description:
Whether RouterLink should not wrap its content in an `a` tag. Useful when
using `v-slot` to create a custom RouterLink

props.name: ariaCurrentValue
props.description: Value passed to the attribute `aria-current` when the link is exact active.

props.name: replace
props.description: Calls `router.replace` instead of `router.push`.

props.name: target
props.description: Where to display the linked URL, as the name for a browsing context.

props.name: rel
props.description: A rel attribute value to apply on the link. Defaults to "noopener noreferrer" for external links.

props.name: noRel
props.description: If set to true, no rel attribute will be added to the link

props.name: prefetch
props.description: When enabled will prefetch middleware, layouts and payloads of links in the viewport.

props.name: noPrefetch
props.description: Escape hatch to disable `prefetch` attribute.

props.name: external
props.description: Forces the link to be considered as external (true) or internal (false). This is helpful to handle edge-cases

props.name: href
props.description: An alias for `to`. If used with `to`, `href` will be ignored

props.name: contents
props.description: List of content to be grouped

_path.name: _path
_path.description: Content path, this path is source agnostic and it the content my live in any source

_type.name: _type
_type.description: File type of the content, i.e `markdown`

_file.name: _file
_file.description: Path to the file relative to the content directory

props.name: depth
props.description: Maximum heading depth to include in the TOC

props.name: links
